  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Building Capacity for Sustainable Livelihoods and Health through Public-Private Linkages in Agriculture and Health Systems</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will provide resources and training that will strengthen individual and collective capabilities to build social capital and improve health among rural families. Interventions will diversify participants&#x2019; income-generating activities with poultry and beekeeping, and introduce efficient irrigation systems to enable farmers to cultivate vegetables during the dry season.
Additionally, women-led self-help groups will be formed to provide support and strengthen inter-institutional communications. Trainings on sanitation and hygiene will improve the local environment and foster maternal and child health.</narrative>
  </description>
